data.title: Joseph Andrews
data.meta_description:
Joseph-andrews.doc - Free download as Word Doc (.doc), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. 1) Joseph Andrews is a picaresque novel that follows the journey of Joseph Andrews and Parson Adams through a series of confusing episodes. 

2) The novel moves from the hypocrisy of London to the open sincerity of the country. Fielding aligns the characters with their correct partners in an improved social setting by the end.

3) Parson Adams emerges as the most fully developed character, acting as a positive force through his virtues of charity, sincerity and active goodness. He redeems the novel from the hypocrites that populate its pages.
